# Code Architecture

## Overview

The system is structured as a modular Python application with clear separation between:

- Data models
- logic (progression engine)
- Application services
- Persistence layer

---

## Architectural Principles

- Separation of concerns
- Stateless business logic
- Explicit data models
- saved File-based (MVP)
- Testable progression engine

---

## Module Breakdown

### models/

Defines core domain objects.

- Exercise
- ExercisePrescription
- Program
- WorkoutSession
- SetResult

These are pure data structures (dataclasses).

---

### engine/

Contains progression logic.

#### progression.py
Implements deterministic progression rules.

#### autoregulation.py
Implements RPE/RIR-based adjustments.

#### updater.py
Combines outputs into next program.

---

### services/

Orchestrates workflows.

#### program_service.py
- Creates programs
- Calls progression engine

#### session_service.py
- Handles workout logging
- Validates session structure

---

### storage/

Handles persistence layer.

#### file_storage.py
- Save/load JSON files

#### repository.py
- Abstraction over storage

---

### utils/

Helper functions such as:
- volume calculations
- load progression math

---

### main.py

Entry point for:
- running program generation
- simulating workout cycle
- testing engine manually

---

## Design Philosophy

- Models contain no logic
- Engine contains all decision-making
- Services coordinate flow
- Storage is replaceable
